item.description:
Rationale: - I had to extend angular material paginator by showing a few page numbers between the prev/next buttons. Unfortunately Angular material gives few extension points. I decided to go on top of their implementation integrating my changes into the library source code.
Environment: - framework -&gt; &ldquo;@angular&rdquo;: &ldquo;^7.0.0&rdquo;, - dependencies -&gt; &ldquo;@angular/material&rdquo;: &ldquo;^7.0.1&rdquo;
The page links are a separate dummy component with only presentational duties. They communicate back when the user clicks by emitting an event with the their index as a payload.
